		  <p>“Customer satisfaction” is a good way to sell shoes; but it is a bad way to relieve ignorance. It is fundamentally stupid to base the content of an education on what the as-yet uneducated person decides is best. </p>
		  <p>– Matthew Stewart,  the book <cite>The Management Myth: Why the Experts Keep Getting it Wrong</cite>, 2009</p>
